dcterms:description: A benchmark for crowd counting containing 1,198 scene images and 330,165 labeled head positions, subdivided into PartA (A) and PartB (B). PartA is densely populated with 300 training images and 182 testing images, while PartB is relatively sparser with 400 training images and 316 testing images.

dcterms:description: A challenging crowd counting dataset with rich scenes and varying viewpoints, densities, and illumination conditions. It contains 1,535 images of dense crowd scenes, with 1,201 training images and 334 testing images.

dcterms:description: A large-scale benchmark for crowd counting and localization, containing 5,109 high-resolution images and annotated entities totaling 2,133,238. The dataset presents a large range of annotated entity numbers for a single image, making it extremely challenging.
dcterms:title: NWPU-Crowd
